    "causal_summary": "memory_save commits the primary memory row inside writeTransaction.immediate(), then runs secondary enrichment (FTS, vector, entity/summary, causal/graph) in a separate phase. A SIGKILL between the commit and enrichment completing leaves the row durably present but unenriched; the next save of the same content short-circuits via primary-row dedup (unchanged/duplicate) and never repairs the missing enrichment, so the memory stays invisible to FTS/vector/graph search until an unrelated scan re-indexes it. This packet adds a durable per-row enrichment-completion marker (schema v30: status/state/completed_at/version columns, default complete for back-compat) written pending inside the primary transaction and flipped to complete after enrichment, plus idempotent repair on the dedup replay path and a bounded backfill under the scan lease. Production stays on v29; the v30 migration is unit-tested on a branch and deployed only on a separate confirmed daemon restart.",
